China’s Hog Breeding Is ‘Firmly Bouncing Back,’ Ministry Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-29T02:07:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/china-s-hog-breeding-is-firmly-bouncing-back-ministry-says.html
China ’s hog herds are “firmly
bouncing back,” with the total number of pigs rising for six
months and the number of breeding sows rising for four months,
the Ministry of Agriculture said in a statement distributed
today before a briefing in Beijing.  The number of pigs to be slaughtered will gradually
increase, ensuring supplies of pork, the ministry said in the
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
